  ;; Nodes
  {:el :regulation
   :id :regulation.eu/dora
   :name "DORA"
   :desc "The Digital Operational Resilience Act (DORA) aims to strengthen the digital operational resilience of financial entities."
   :doc "The Digital Operational Resilience Act (DORA) is a regulation that
         aims to strengthen the digital operational resilience of financial
         entities. It establishes a comprehensive framework for the management
         of ICT risks, including requirements for ICT risk management, incident
         reporting, digital operational resilience testing, and information
         sharing. DORA applies to a wide range of financial entities, including
         banks, insurance companies, investment firms, and payment service
         providers."}

  {:el :regulation
   :id :regulation.eu/gdpr
   :name "GDPR"
   :desc "The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) aims to protect the privacy and personal data of individuals."
   :doc "The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is a regulation that
         aims to protect the privacy and personal data of individuals in the
         European Union. It establishes rules for the collection, processing,
         and storage of personal data, and grants individuals certain rights
         regarding their personal data. The GDPR applies to organizations that
         process personal data of individuals in the EU, regardless of where
         the organization is located."}

  {:el :regulation
   :id :regulation.eu/cloud-act
   :name "Cloud Act"
   :desc "The Clarifying Lawful Overseas Use of Data Act (Cloud Act) aims to clarify the legal framework for cross-border data access and sharing."
   :doc "The Clarifying Lawful Overseas Use of Data Act (Cloud Act) is a
         regulation that aims to clarify the legal framework for cross-border
         data access and sharing. It establishes rules for the access and
         disclosure of data stored by service providers in foreign countries,
         and provides a legal basis for law enforcement agencies to request
         data from service providers. The Cloud Act applies to service
         providers that store data in the United States, as well as to foreign
         service providers that have a substantial connection to the United
         States."}

  {:el :regulation
   :id :regulation.eu/ai-act
   :name "AI Act"
   :desc "The AI Act aims to establish a legal framework for artificial intelligence (AI)."
   :doc "The AI Act is a proposed regulation by the European Commission that
         aims to establish a legal framework for artificial intelligence (AI)
         in the European Union. The regulation seeks to ensure that AI systems
         are safe, transparent, and respect fundamental rights. It introduces a
         risk-based approach to AI regulation, categorizing AI systems into
         different risk levels and imposing corresponding obligations on
         providers and users of AI systems."}

